contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:30.233 --> 00:32.232
You're almost there.
Don't push.

00:33.233 --> 00:35.499
You're the closest.
Don't push yet, don't push.

00:35.500 --> 00:37.232
You're almost there though.

00:37.233 --> 00:41.033
Don't push. Breathe.
Just breathe. It's almost over.

00:42.767 --> 00:44.499
You're not quite there.

00:44.500 --> 00:47.200
You have a little while.
You're not there. Calm, calm.

00:50.333 --> 00:51.333
You're almost there.

00:53.100 --> 00:55.633
Breathe.
You're close, just breathe.

00:58.767 --> 00:59.767
I can't!

01:00.400 --> 01:02.200
I can see the head.

01:07.333 --> 01:09.532
Sweetheart, look at me.
One last push!

01:11.600 --> 01:14.600
That's it. It's here! It's here.

01:16.333 --> 01:17.333
My baby!

01:18.567 --> 01:21.100
- Your son is here, Natalie.
- Oh, my God!

01:21.633 --> 01:23.033
He's so beautiful!

01:26.833 --> 01:28.432
It's almost time.

01:32.433 --> 01:35.332
Push! You're fully dilated.

01:35.333 --> 01:38.232
Push! Push it now!

01:38.233 --> 01:39.432
Again!

01:40.667 --> 01:42.733
Hold still, you can do this!

01:43.433 --> 01:46.267
- You're fully dilated. Push!
- I know!

01:46.667 --> 01:47.732
All right. I'm gonna help you.

01:47.733 --> 01:49.466
This is gonna hurt
for one moment.

01:49.467 --> 01:50.533
Get it out!

01:51.333 --> 01:53.566
- What're you trying do to?
- I'm gonna do it for you!

01:53.567 --> 01:54.567
Push!

01:55.833 --> 01:57.732
- I hate you!
- It's coming.

01:57.733 --> 02:01.000
- I hate you!
- The head is coming out. Push!

02:03.600 --> 02:05.299
It's coming.

02:07.133 --> 02:09.433
You did it. The baby!

02:11.400 --> 02:15.333
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God! Push!
- What?

02:18.433 --> 02:19.433
Second's in...

02:26.700 --> 02:28.667
- You have twins.
- What?

02:29.300 --> 02:30.633
You had two babies.

02:34.200 --> 02:36.767
- Hold your baby, Staci.
- I don't want to see it.

02:40.833 --> 02:44.267
- Hold your baby, Staci.
- No! No!

03:13.233 --> 03:18.567
Dr. Wise, I'm in so much pain
that I'm nauseous!

03:22.400 --> 03:24.033
The girls are so peaceful!

03:25.567 --> 03:28.600
Oh, why does it hurts so much?
Something's wrong!

03:30.233 --> 03:32.067
These babies have been
such a curse.

03:41.367 --> 03:42.400
It's impossible.

03:46.333 --> 03:49.567
- Impossible.
- What? What's impossible?

03:54.533 --> 03:55.567
It can't be.

04:03.133 --> 04:04.167
You're...

04:07.333 --> 04:08.333
You're pregnant.

04:11.433 --> 04:16.433
No! No, it can't be.
That's impossible. It can't be.

04:19.333 --> 04:21.333
Oh, yes. It can be.

04:23.300 --> 04:24.333
When you're in hell.

04:31.200 --> 04:35.133
I died on the operating table
at the abortion clinic.

04:37.533 --> 04:39.133
I committed suicide.

04:42.400 --> 04:47.500
Welcome to your eternity,
Dr. Wise, Staci.

04:48.633 --> 04:51.400
Prepare for another nine months.

05:07.767 --> 05:08.767
Well?

05:13.467 --> 05:14.599
You're the foreman.

05:14.600 --> 05:16.699
It's up to you
to get things moving.

05:16.700 --> 05:18.200
Okay, I'll do a count.

05:18.600 --> 05:21.832
Uh... You guys good with hands,
show of hands?

05:21.833 --> 05:23.033
- Sure.
- Why not?

05:24.367 --> 05:25.832
- Shall I write this on a pad?
- Yeah.

05:25.833 --> 05:27.599
Look,
we all know they're guilty.

05:27.600 --> 05:29.232
They kidnapped the girl.

05:29.233 --> 05:31.332
So, let's just vote
and get this over with.

05:31.333 --> 05:32.799
All right, fine.

05:32.800 --> 05:34.533
Raise your hands
if you say guilty.

05:41.700 --> 05:44.000
Okay, that's 11 for guilty.
Not guilty?

05:47.367 --> 05:49.399
Not guilty? Are you serious?

05:49.400 --> 05:50.666
I can't deal with this today.

05:50.667 --> 05:53.066
I've got a major business
dinner at seven.

05:53.067 --> 05:55.166
It's pretty clear
to the rest of us.

05:55.167 --> 05:57.033
Did everyone really
think this through?

05:57.700 --> 06:00.599
Or are you just deciding
based on emotion?

06:00.600 --> 06:03.432
What's to think through?
We have confessions!

06:03.433 --> 06:05.666
That's a luxury
in most criminal cases.

06:05.667 --> 06:07.266
Not only confessions,

06:07.267 --> 06:10.266
but we have a video tape
of the actual crime.

06:10.267 --> 06:12.366
For seven months,
24 hours a day,

06:12.367 --> 06:13.766
they filmed themselves.

06:13.767 --> 06:15.666
Which jury gets
that kind of evidence?

06:15.667 --> 06:18.133
I thought through this case
during the entire trial.

06:18.567 --> 06:20.132
All the while watching

06:20.133 --> 06:22.466
the hours of footage
of their crime,

06:22.467 --> 06:24.566
and listening to
their testimony.

06:24.567 --> 06:26.599
I don't need to
think about it anymore.

06:26.600 --> 06:28.099
Oh, what's there to think
about, really?

06:28.100 --> 06:29.600
I mean, the law is the law.

06:30.267 --> 06:32.266
We had plenty of time
to think about this

06:32.267 --> 06:35.200
and we're all in agreement.
Except you.

06:35.600 --> 06:37.667
- Why is it so cold in here?
- Yeah, it's freezing.

06:38.600 --> 06:40.566
Thank God I wore this sweater.

06:40.567 --> 06:42.799
Can we call somebody
to come fix the heat?

06:42.800 --> 06:45.266
Our tax dollars at work, right?
You know, you'd think

06:45.267 --> 06:46.599
that the government
could at least afford

06:46.600 --> 06:48.732
to heat their own buildings.

06:48.733 --> 06:49.733
I'll take a look.

06:50.767 --> 06:52.132
Look, I'll call a bailiff

06:52.133 --> 06:53.732
and have him call maintenance,
all right?

06:53.733 --> 06:56.232
Let's just get back
to the vote, people.

06:56.233 --> 06:57.399
Let's hope we're out
of here soon.

06:57.400 --> 06:58.467
It won't even matter.

06:59.500 --> 07:01.666
Well, we don't have
a unanimous decision yet,

07:01.667 --> 07:04.166
so, looks like
we're not going anywhere.

07:04.167 --> 07:05.333
Look, everyone.

07:06.567 --> 07:08.466
I'm not saying that you didn't
think about what you heard.

07:08.467 --> 07:10.500
I'm just raising
the logical question.

07:11.467 --> 07:13.832
Are you saying guilty
out of emotion?

07:13.833 --> 07:16.466
Or because you truly believe
legally

07:16.467 --> 07:19.099
and morally
that they are guilty?

07:19.100 --> 07:20.199
All right,
let's just think about

07:20.200 --> 07:23.199
this thing for a minute, okay?
Let's talk this out.

07:23.200 --> 07:25.399
Does anyone have
anything to say?

07:25.400 --> 07:28.199
Honey, why don't you just tell
us what you're thinking,

07:28.200 --> 07:30.099
so we... So we all understand?

07:30.100 --> 07:32.299
Yeah, maybe we can help you
out of your confusion,

07:32.300 --> 07:34.666
and you can realize
that they are guilty.

07:34.667 --> 07:36.666
Since we've had
our minds made up,

07:36.667 --> 07:39.200
why don't we try to explain
to her our thought processes?

07:39.633 --> 07:42.333
We are in majority.
We have to convince her.

07:43.167 --> 07:45.532
It's a good idea.
Why don't we go around the table

07:45.533 --> 07:47.200
and see
what everyone has to say?

07:48.267 --> 07:49.467
Anybody want to start?

07:51.333 --> 07:52.600
We might as well go in order.

07:54.300 --> 07:56.299
No, I'm the foreman,
so, I'll go last,

07:56.300 --> 07:58.300
but you are number two,
why don't you start?

08:00.200 --> 08:02.266
You know,
there's a reason courtrooms

08:02.267 --> 08:05.033
have that justice statue
with a blindfold, right?

08:05.467 --> 08:07.699
It's because justice
is based on facts

08:07.700 --> 08:10.000
and the facts are,
they are guilty.

08:10.467 --> 08:12.500
We have videotape
and confessions.

08:13.700 --> 08:14.767
What more do you want?

08:15.733 --> 08:17.732
I know what the facts are,

08:17.733 --> 08:20.400
and I know how it looks to
the people in this room,

08:20.833 --> 08:23.166
but I am saying that they are
not guilty

08:23.167 --> 08:25.200
because I believe
the law says so.

08:27.400 --> 08:28.500
Maybe they were justified?

08:29.333 --> 08:30.699
What, now you're with her?

08:30.700 --> 08:32.400
I'm just asking a question.

08:33.366 --> 08:35.500
You saw Staci's two children,
the twins, testify.

08:36.500 --> 08:37.799
They'd be dead if Dr. Wise

08:37.799 --> 08:39.799
and the others
didn't kidnap Staci.

08:39.799 --> 08:41.366
Not born.

08:41.366 --> 08:43.332
- Huh?
- They're not dead.

08:43.332 --> 08:46.133
They're just not yet born.
There's a huge difference.

08:46.567 --> 08:47.600
Are you crazy?

08:48.600 --> 08:51.232
Staci Horowitz wanted to
have an abortion

08:51.233 --> 08:52.499
two months into her pregnancy,

08:52.500 --> 08:55.166
and she had
a legal right to do so.

08:55.167 --> 08:56.499
And these maniacs kidnapped her,

08:56.500 --> 08:57.366
making her stay in a place

08:57.367 --> 08:59.400
that was probably colder
than in here.

09:00.200 --> 09:03.466
For seven months,
they incarcerated her,

09:03.467 --> 09:05.599
and they played mind games
with the poor girl.

09:05.600 --> 09:07.499
Christ! They even tried to
make her think

09:07.500 --> 09:09.333
she was in hell
after she gave birth!

09:10.433 --> 09:12.732
Come on, you two.
Get your senses together.

09:12.733 --> 09:14.299
You can't hold us up here.

09:14.300 --> 09:16.566
It's like you're kidnapping
us right now.

09:16.567 --> 09:18.332
I just asked a question,
all right?

09:18.333 --> 09:20.133
I'm not holding anything up.

09:20.633 --> 09:23.232
He made a good point about
just how purposeful

09:23.233 --> 09:24.432
and plotting these people were.

09:24.433 --> 09:26.673
Those are the kind of things
the prosecutor talked about.

09:27.667 --> 09:29.432
They planned
the kidnapping form months.

09:29.433 --> 09:31.233
They rehearsed and rehearsed.

09:32.067 --> 09:33.567
Tried to manipulate
Ms. Horowitz.

09:34.267 --> 09:36.166
There's tons of footage.

09:36.167 --> 09:37.599
You should be able
to find something

09:37.600 --> 09:39.466
that shows plotting
and manipulation.

09:39.467 --> 09:41.332
I'm one step ahead of you.

09:41.333 --> 09:42.799
I didn't say that they didn't
plan it out.

09:42.800 --> 09:45.132
- I'm just saying we should...
- Here.

09:45.133 --> 09:46.133
Watch this again.

09:53.600 --> 09:57.300
No, no, no, no!

10:11.333 --> 10:13.567
You were all
on the operating table.

10:15.267 --> 10:17.267
All ready to commit murder.

10:19.300 --> 10:23.067
And now, your babies
will be given life,

10:23.467 --> 10:25.133
just as God planned.

10:29.533 --> 10:32.267
You're nuts.
You kidnapped us!

10:34.067 --> 10:36.233
Lara,
the strongest of the three.

10:37.800 --> 10:40.400
Strong has nothing to do
with my anger.

10:41.533 --> 10:45.000
You violated my most precious
of constitutional rights!

10:45.467 --> 10:48.667
What about the child's rights?
God's rights?

10:50.700 --> 10:52.200
Please, stop the craziness.

10:54.133 --> 10:57.567
Maybe, she's right.
What about the child's rights?

10:58.333 --> 11:00.233
I was pressured into this
by Brandon.

11:01.667 --> 11:03.832
I appreciate the support,
Natalie,

11:03.833 --> 11:05.600
but you shouldn't slam Brandon.

11:06.833 --> 11:09.200
You're an adult woman.
You made the choice.

11:11.233 --> 11:12.300
Come here, child.

11:20.067 --> 11:22.167
You decided to kill your baby.

11:23.700 --> 11:25.300
Brandon couldn't make you,
could he?

11:27.600 --> 11:30.200
Don't be weak, Natalie.
This is a cult.

11:32.167 --> 11:35.199
Fanatics! You're a
throwback to 50 years ago

11:35.200 --> 11:37.066
with all this
radical Christianity!

11:37.067 --> 11:39.300
Your goal is to discriminate
against women.

11:40.367 --> 11:41.467
I am a woman.

11:42.233 --> 11:44.399
Don't use your femininity
as a crutch.

11:44.400 --> 11:46.399
You stand for nothing
about gender equality,

11:46.400 --> 11:49.200
when you want to take away
our most basic freedom.

11:50.067 --> 11:53.300
Looks as if I was wrong,
Staci is the strongest.

11:54.333 --> 11:57.132
I don't care about
who's the strongest,

11:57.133 --> 12:00.532
and I don't care about
this stupid political debate!

12:00.533 --> 12:03.200
I'm gonna get to the point.
What do you want from us?

12:04.233 --> 12:06.033
Lara, the typical lawyer.

12:07.400 --> 12:09.700
What do you want from us?

12:11.600 --> 12:12.667
Not want...

12:18.833 --> 12:21.633
demand. You will stay here,

12:22.233 --> 12:25.466
in this room,
for the next seven months,

12:25.467 --> 12:29.500
until you all simultaneously
give birth to your children.

12:31.500 --> 12:34.367
I... I still can't believe that
she was part of the kidnapping.

12:34.833 --> 12:38.000
- Who? Dr. Wise or Lara Foley?
- Lara Foley.

12:38.467 --> 12:40.233
She just seemed so authentic.

12:40.733 --> 12:42.267
Yeah, so did Natalie.

12:43.400 --> 12:46.399
Hey! They all confessed.

12:46.400 --> 12:48.733
They're right wing nuts.
They're like terrorists.

12:49.333 --> 12:51.432
Instead of training with
machine guns and bombs,

12:51.433 --> 12:53.199
they trained in acting.

12:53.200 --> 12:55.532
They spent months getting
into their characters,

12:55.533 --> 12:58.233
and going over some "loose
script", as they called it.

12:59.433 --> 13:02.100
But there was so much that
couldn't have been scripted.

13:02.733 --> 13:04.432
In fact, most of it.

13:04.433 --> 13:06.200
It was a general idea, get it?

13:08.267 --> 13:10.300
I can take out that
silly church doctor.

13:12.633 --> 13:15.200
Lara? Lara?

13:18.633 --> 13:21.300
The three of us can easily
eliminate her.

13:22.333 --> 13:24.600
You don't know what's
behind that door or who.

13:26.400 --> 13:29.199
There could be no one.
There probably is no one.

13:29.200 --> 13:31.733
All we've seen is that woman,
and the suit on the TV.

13:33.833 --> 13:35.600
And what if there are
more out there?

13:38.200 --> 13:40.533
Don't you get it?
They're not gonna hurt us.

13:41.467 --> 13:44.133
They can't hurt us because
they won't hurt the babies.

13:49.333 --> 13:52.767
She is a scared little girl,
but you and I are women.

13:53.600 --> 13:54.600
Come on.

13:55.367 --> 13:58.300
I'm scared too
and what if that fence is real?

14:01.067 --> 14:02.167
I'll try to cross it.

14:04.533 --> 14:09.566
Look, I know you're frightened,

14:09.567 --> 14:13.099
terrified and I know that you
feel guilty about the abortion,

14:13.100 --> 14:15.400
but you're just buying into
their propaganda.

14:15.833 --> 14:17.599
They're brainwashing us.

14:17.600 --> 14:21.232
I really do think that what
I was about to do was wrong.

14:21.233 --> 14:23.133
You weren't doing
anything wrong!

14:23.833 --> 14:28.332
Let's say we eliminate Dr. Wise

14:28.333 --> 14:30.332
and there's no one else here
with her.

14:30.333 --> 14:31.333
Then we're home free.

14:32.800 --> 14:36.432
Maybe, maybe there's
a phone or computer

14:36.433 --> 14:37.799
and we can contact help.

14:37.800 --> 14:41.099
- Yeah.
- But maybe not.

14:41.100 --> 14:43.432
And you try to run into
the snow, desert,

14:43.433 --> 14:45.233
wilderness,
wherever the hell we are,

14:46.667 --> 14:47.667
and you pass out.

14:48.667 --> 14:51.567
Natalie and I can't help you
for the same reason.

14:52.467 --> 14:55.099
We can't help you because
we'd pass out trying.

14:55.100 --> 14:58.067
Yes, and then you'll die in
the snow and so will your baby.

14:58.800 --> 15:00.133
My baby?

15:01.267 --> 15:05.266
I don't have a baby,
you stupid little girl!

15:05.267 --> 15:06.266
I don't have
anything inside of me

15:06.267 --> 15:08.799
I that even remotely resembles
a human being!

15:08.800 --> 15:10.600
And neither do you,
nor does Lara!

15:11.767 --> 15:14.000
Staci, I agree with you.

15:14.533 --> 15:16.667
There's gonna be a lot of
brainwashing going on here.

15:18.400 --> 15:21.266
I got to say I'm pretty impressed
with the performances.

15:21.267 --> 15:24.432
I mean, these girls definitely
seem like kidnap victims to me.

15:24.433 --> 15:27.066
But they weren't!
We've got confessions, remember?

15:27.067 --> 15:28.599
And they all testified,

15:28.600 --> 15:32.466
right in front of us at trial
admitting their damn atrocities.

15:32.467 --> 15:36.033
Calm down, man. You don't act
to the foreman that way.

15:36.600 --> 15:39.567
I just want to understand what
we're wasting time here for.

15:40.167 --> 15:41.467
They're all obviously guilty.

15:42.300 --> 15:46.066
Robert Lation,
Dr. Victoria Wise, Lara Foley,

15:46.067 --> 15:48.266
and that young girl,
Natalie Fields.

15:48.267 --> 15:51.567
All guilty of kidnapping
Staci Horowitz.

15:52.200 --> 15:54.299
I don't see
how anyone can disagree.

15:54.300 --> 15:56.599
It's the most open and
shut case I've ever seen.

15:56.600 --> 15:57.799
You're correct.

15:57.800 --> 15:59.132
They've told the police
they kidnapped her

15:59.133 --> 16:00.466
and they've told us.

16:00.467 --> 16:02.699
And they had surveillance
cameras up 24/7

16:02.700 --> 16:07.066
for the entire seven months,
so, we can see the entire show.

16:07.067 --> 16:09.832
I don't have seven months
to watch the whole show, okay?

16:09.833 --> 16:11.466
I think we saw enough
of it at trial.

16:11.467 --> 16:13.600
It's not a show.
It's a kidnapping.

16:14.400 --> 16:16.467
It's a terrible crime against
that poor woman.

16:17.700 --> 16:20.732
You're right, of course.
It was no Broadway play.

16:20.733 --> 16:22.566
Look, I attended for a year

16:22.567 --> 16:24.366
at a law school
before I changed my mind

16:24.367 --> 16:25.633
and went to medical school.

16:26.633 --> 16:28.466
Criminal law 101 says

16:28.467 --> 16:31.467
that we have to look for
mens rea. The intent.

16:33.167 --> 16:35.567
They all had the intent to
commit this crime.

16:36.200 --> 16:38.699
So, it's up to us
to convict them.

16:38.700 --> 16:41.367
You are all talking about their
intent and their planning.

16:42.367 --> 16:44.267
Look at why they planned this.

16:45.200 --> 16:47.066
Their purpose
was to prevent Staci

16:47.067 --> 16:48.167
from aborting her children.

16:48.700 --> 16:50.732
Roe V. Wade has not
been reversed.

16:50.733 --> 16:53.000
She has the right to have
an abortion. It's still legal.

16:54.300 --> 16:56.832
Are you saying it's okay
to commit crimes

16:56.833 --> 16:59.367
to keep people from doing things
you don't agree with?

17:00.400 --> 17:03.799
Imagine our society
if everybody acted that way.

17:03.800 --> 17:06.531
Whoa, whoa, hold on a second.
Do you have kids?

17:06.532 --> 17:08.400
Yes. Why?

17:09.099 --> 17:11.199
Wouldn't you do
anything you could

17:11.200 --> 17:13.699
to stop somebody trying to
hurt your kids?

17:13.700 --> 17:16.199
I mean, even if it meant
risking getting arrested

17:16.200 --> 17:18.000
and getting charged with
assault or something?

17:18.800 --> 17:21.531
I would, no question.
Who wouldn't?

17:21.532 --> 17:24.398
So, how does that make
these defendants justified?

17:24.400 --> 17:26.799
Wait a minute,
there is a huge difference here.

17:26.800 --> 17:29.066
I love my kids and I would
do anything for them,

17:29.067 --> 17:32.067
but they are actually in
this world. They are alive.

17:32.700 --> 17:34.566
When she was kidnapped,
Staci Horowitz's children,

17:34.567 --> 17:36.566
they were not even born yet.

17:36.567 --> 17:39.266
Yeah, you're saying it's okay
to commit crimes

17:39.267 --> 17:41.432
to protect people
that don't exist?

17:41.433 --> 17:43.000
What do you mean, "don't exist"?

17:43.800 --> 17:47.066
Her children were very much
alive inside her womb.

17:47.067 --> 17:48.566
You're telling me
that you consider them

17:48.567 --> 17:50.432
children at that point?

17:50.433 --> 17:54.200
They... They were fetuses,
masses of cells.

