you didn't raise your hand
for either.

33:28.833 --> 33:31.600
He's right.
Well, sir, what's your vote?

33:33.367 --> 33:35.799
As you said, you're the one
who's been charged

33:35.800 --> 33:39.400
with being in control here,
keeping things orderly.

33:40.467 --> 33:42.666
This is not setting
a good example.

33:42.667 --> 33:46.000
You're correct.
This has just gotten difficult.

33:46.500 --> 33:49.033
- It's not difficult to me.
- Certainly not to me!

33:49.467 --> 33:51.532
Some of you have just gone
completely off the deep end

33:51.533 --> 33:53.573
because of this radical,
little Christian girl here.

33:54.600 --> 33:56.433
I've my own mind, all right?

33:57.067 --> 33:58.766
Now, she might have made
a few good points

33:58.767 --> 34:00.499
which others built on,

34:00.500 --> 34:02.766
and the judge
with his few words solidified,

34:02.767 --> 34:05.599
but, for me,
it was this young lady.

34:05.600 --> 34:06.699
Me?

34:06.700 --> 34:07.740
Yes, ma'am. You.

34:09.367 --> 34:13.132
You have succinctly
summarized it. At least, for me.

34:15.567 --> 34:17.766
So, I have to change
my vote to not guilty.

34:18.667 --> 34:21.831
I don't believe this. I'm gonna
push back my business meeting.

34:21.833 --> 34:24.331
What is so important
about this business meeting?

34:24.333 --> 34:27.132
You keep talking about it.
What is so important about it?

34:27.132 --> 34:30.366
None of your business.
Do you like that? Huh? Huh?

34:30.367 --> 34:32.266
That's a double entendre.

34:32.266 --> 34:34.831
I'm using business
in two different ways.

34:34.833 --> 34:37.132
You're acting like a moron.

34:37.132 --> 34:39.565
Let's go back to what
we were doing before, okay?

34:39.567 --> 34:40.732
Going around the table

34:40.733 --> 34:43.331
and each giving our argument
about why they are guilty.

34:43.333 --> 34:45.766
There was so much clarity when
we walked out of that courtroom

34:45.766 --> 34:47.532
and first walked into this room.

34:47.533 --> 34:50.232
Very true. I believe
if we can actually focus

34:50.233 --> 34:52.199
on the law of kidnapping itself,

34:52.199 --> 34:54.065
this can become
very simple again.

34:54.067 --> 34:56.099
And you, or some of you,

34:56.100 --> 34:58.467
who have changed your vote
to not guilty

34:59.367 --> 35:01.767
will go back very quickly
to guilty.

35:02.533 --> 35:05.566
Even me?
Who was never at guilty?

35:05.567 --> 35:07.532
It seems that you have
a special understanding

35:07.533 --> 35:09.300
of the law, my dear.

35:09.767 --> 35:11.567
I hope that the legal reasons

35:12.300 --> 35:14.799
shed some light on you
and your way of thinking.

35:14.800 --> 35:17.232
There is a light
at the end of this tunnel

35:17.233 --> 35:19.766
and I believe
that you will ultimately see it.

35:19.767 --> 35:21.533
Can we disband
the light analogies?

35:23.300 --> 35:24.300
I believe I'm next.

35:25.400 --> 35:28.066
Given that only
juror number two had spoken

35:28.067 --> 35:30.532
when we were presenting our
arguments in a systematic,

35:30.533 --> 35:32.399
organized manner.

35:32.400 --> 35:34.600
Well said!
Let's get a move on this.

35:35.467 --> 35:36.700
They are guilty

35:37.433 --> 35:42.332
because they have violated
Staci's basic rights

35:42.333 --> 35:44.767
to life, liberty,
the pursuit of happiness.

35:46.100 --> 35:50.666
They took away her way of life
as she knew it, and liberty.

35:50.667 --> 35:54.267
Forget liberty, she was stuck
in a room for seven months!

35:55.100 --> 35:58.332
Now, let's take an exact look at
what Robert Lation,

35:58.333 --> 35:59.733
the ringleader
of the kidnapping...

36:02.733 --> 36:05.599
had to say about his role in it.

36:06.800 --> 36:10.767
Do not speak.
Do not say a word.

36:12.467 --> 36:14.766
You not only have the right
to remain silent...

36:15.900 --> 36:21.067
...you will remain silent
while I speak. Understood?

36:22.533 --> 36:25.600
- Yes.
- I said remain silent.

36:27.333 --> 36:32.100
Now, you're probably
wondering who I am.

36:33.167 --> 36:35.332
The same as you wondering

36:35.333 --> 36:38.433
who the other women are
who're standing with you.

36:39.467 --> 36:42.700
Same as you're wondering
where you are,

36:43.367 --> 36:48.733
the same as you're wondering
why you are where you are.

36:52.833 --> 36:59.267
You have all committed
a terrible sin.

37:01.533 --> 37:06.600
Ah, Ms. Posey,
you're the first to realize.

37:09.700 --> 37:14.733
Think of me as a member
of the criminal justice system.

37:16.167 --> 37:19.133
Unfortunately for you,
I'm not a lawyer.

37:20.067 --> 37:23.166
Nor I am the police,
nor a prosecutor

37:23.167 --> 37:25.333
and alas, I'm not the judge.

37:26.567 --> 37:29.600
No, I'm not your judge, ladies.

37:30.833 --> 37:34.533
I am... your jailer.

37:36.167 --> 37:38.067
Calls himself their jailer.

37:39.333 --> 37:42.233
Under the law, if you jail
someone against her will,

37:43.167 --> 37:45.233
you're guilty of kidnapping.

37:46.067 --> 37:49.266
- It's as clear as that.
- Of course, it is. Great point.

37:49.267 --> 37:51.266
These girls, they weren't even
allowed to speak

37:51.267 --> 37:52.699
unless they were
given permission.

37:52.700 --> 37:54.432
- Girl.
- Huh?

37:54.433 --> 37:56.267
Girl. Singular, remember?

37:56.767 --> 37:58.633
Staci Horowitz,
who was kidnapped.

37:59.500 --> 38:02.300
Lara Posey and Laura Fields
were a part of the crime.

38:03.100 --> 38:06.132
I know, that's right.
I... Yes.

38:06.133 --> 38:08.799
These girls were just pretending
to be in this hell with her.

38:08.800 --> 38:13.166
Oh, please. Cry me a river!
This was barely hell.

38:13.167 --> 38:16.099
Staci was fed well, clothed,
she had medical care

38:16.100 --> 38:18.099
and she wasn't in
a freezing room like this.

38:18.100 --> 38:19.267
At least they had heat.

38:19.800 --> 38:20.899
You want to see hell?

38:20.900 --> 38:23.399
Come to my empty bed
every night. Now, that's hell!

38:24.400 --> 38:25.799
Please, don't diminish
what happened to her.

38:25.800 --> 38:27.767
She was held captive
for seven months.

38:28.400 --> 38:30.699
You know, comfortable
accommodations or not.

38:30.700 --> 38:33.167
Well, let's also get
all the facts straight.

38:34.133 --> 38:36.532
Robert Lation was the only one
they had to ask permission

38:36.533 --> 38:38.632
to speak,
and he wasn't around that often.

38:38.633 --> 38:39.666
Other than him,

38:39.667 --> 38:42.299
they were allowed to speak
freely at all times.

38:42.300 --> 38:44.532
In fact,
they were encouraged to have

38:44.533 --> 38:46.566
thoughtful discussions
about abortion.

38:46.567 --> 38:48.600
Both pro-life and pro-choice.

38:50.067 --> 38:51.466
This tells us a lot.

38:52.733 --> 38:54.467
Before we go any further,

38:55.067 --> 38:57.100
I want you all to really
understand a few things.

39:00.233 --> 39:03.467
Yes. We certainly want
to change your minds.

39:04.233 --> 39:07.432
But we know we can't do that by
shoving things down your throat.

39:07.433 --> 39:11.767
So, you will just be watching
movies and documentaries,

39:12.833 --> 39:15.533
reading books,
hearing experts speak.

39:16.367 --> 39:19.166
You'll hear opinions on both
sides of the coin.

39:19.167 --> 39:21.033
From everyone and everyone.

39:21.733 --> 39:23.666
And then we'll have an
opportunity to do something

39:23.667 --> 39:25.133
that no one really ever has.

39:26.700 --> 39:28.499
We'll have
an abortion think-tank

39:28.500 --> 39:30.033
for the next seven months.

39:31.533 --> 39:33.333
Oh, yes.

39:34.300 --> 39:38.199
Nonstop discussions
and probably arguments

39:38.200 --> 39:40.500
on the wholly
important topic of abortion.

39:43.667 --> 39:47.099
If your minds are changed,
we've had a huge bonus.

39:47.100 --> 39:51.633
If not, that most important
primary goal has still been met.

39:53.733 --> 39:59.067
Natalie, Lara, Staci,
look at me.

40:02.400 --> 40:06.033
We will never hurt you.
I promise you.

40:07.567 --> 40:10.400
As soon as your babies are born,
you'll all be freed.

40:16.133 --> 40:17.432
We should be taking away

40:17.433 --> 40:19.167
two important things
from that segment.

40:20.133 --> 40:22.432
First,
we should be having the same

40:22.433 --> 40:24.199
thoughtful discussion
about abortion.

40:24.200 --> 40:25.666
Just as Dr. Wise said,

40:25.667 --> 40:27.699
discussing both sides
of the coin

40:27.700 --> 40:29.620
so we can really understand
what's at stake here.

40:30.600 --> 40:32.766
And, second,
right from the beginning,

40:32.767 --> 40:35.066
she told Staci
that she wouldn't be harmed

40:35.067 --> 40:37.366
and that she would be freed
as soon as she gave birth

40:37.367 --> 40:38.700
and that's exactly
what happened.

40:39.367 --> 40:41.366
Staci was freed right after she
delivered her babies

40:41.367 --> 40:42.766
and she was never harmed.

40:42.767 --> 40:45.133
Honey, there are many
different kinds of harm.

40:45.667 --> 40:49.500
Having your liberty restrained
constitutes harm under the law.

40:50.267 --> 40:54.499
As for psychological harm,
here, we'll look at this now.

40:56.633 --> 41:01.533
The three of you already had
your chance to choose life. Hmm.

41:03.400 --> 41:04.400
And you failed.

41:06.500 --> 41:10.666
You were told earlier that
you're gonna stay with Dr. Wise

41:10.667 --> 41:14.000
until you give birth and
that will never change.

41:15.700 --> 41:16.700
Dr. Wise?

41:18.533 --> 41:21.199
Should you have any thoughts
of escape,

41:21.200 --> 41:23.399
you should know that you are
hundreds of miles

41:23.400 --> 41:25.566
- from any other people.
- Where are we?

41:25.567 --> 41:27.666
Young lady, kindly understand

41:27.667 --> 41:29.832
that you're never to speak
when I'm with you,

41:29.833 --> 41:32.400
unless I specifically
give you permission!

41:34.533 --> 41:35.633
Dr. Wise.

41:40.700 --> 41:43.067
Lift up the back of your hair.

41:44.333 --> 41:48.033
Touch high up on your neck.
You have bandages there

41:49.233 --> 41:52.433
where I have implanted
small electronic devices.

41:53.700 --> 41:55.766
It was minor laser surgery,

41:55.767 --> 41:58.599
but nonetheless
a necessary procedure

41:58.600 --> 42:01.000
to ensure that we meet
that primary goal.

42:03.300 --> 42:07.567
Now, Staci, do you have a
question? Just one, please.

42:11.833 --> 42:14.199
What are these electronic
devices supposed to do to us?

42:15.367 --> 42:18.267
That's a good question.
Dr. Wise.

42:20.333 --> 42:23.099
Under the unlikely circumstances

42:23.100 --> 42:25.566
that you should escape
this building

42:25.567 --> 42:29.467
into the frost-bitten cold of
night in your little nightgown,

42:30.467 --> 42:32.733
you will pass out within ten
feet of the door.

42:33.500 --> 42:34.767
Any of you have a dog?

42:37.600 --> 42:40.666
You have one of those invisible
electronic fences

42:40.667 --> 42:42.467
that are in your yard
or under the ground?

42:43.767 --> 42:45.732
No. But you all understand

42:45.733 --> 42:48.633
how the invisible
electronic fences work?

42:49.400 --> 42:54.067
Zip! The dog get stung
if it passes the fence.

42:55.167 --> 42:56.167
Dr. Wise.

42:57.467 --> 43:01.533
Well, you won't get stung.
But you will pass out.

43:02.667 --> 43:05.166
Of course,
the baby won't be harmed

43:05.167 --> 43:07.766
as a low voltage
electronic impulse

43:07.767 --> 43:10.766
will release a harmless
anesthetic into your bloodstream

43:10.767 --> 43:13.367
that will temporarily cause you
to lose consciousness

43:13.800 --> 43:15.700
and then we'll retrieve you
from the snow.

43:18.200 --> 43:20.267
Enjoy the accommodations.

43:23.800 --> 43:26.366
Under the law,
I'm sure you'll all agree

43:26.367 --> 43:29.233
that implanting an electronic
device in someone's head

43:30.367 --> 43:34.066
which could cause them to be
rendered unconscious is harmful.

43:34.067 --> 43:36.066
Again, good point.

43:36.067 --> 43:38.367
You both are missing something
here that's critical.

43:38.833 --> 43:41.700
Dr. Wise never implanted
the device in Stacy Horowitz.

43:42.567 --> 43:45.699
After her release, she was
examined by several doctors,

43:45.700 --> 43:47.532
and all their medical reports
came back negative

43:47.533 --> 43:49.167
for any surgeries
performed on her.

43:50.067 --> 43:52.199
The fact is,
it was just a scare tactic.

43:52.200 --> 43:53.799
Yes. But that scare tactic

43:53.800 --> 43:56.732
equates harm as much as a
physical beating.

43:56.733 --> 44:00.400
And months of restraint
causes harm just the same.

44:02.400 --> 44:06.499
Victoria Wise, Robert Lation,
Lara Foley and Natalie Fields

44:06.500 --> 44:08.599
through their illicit
kidnapping conspiracy

44:08.600 --> 44:12.266
are all guilty of
causing Staci Horowitz

44:12.267 --> 44:14.600
to suffer extreme
psychological damages.

44:16.600 --> 44:19.266
But if they hadn't held Staci
for seven months,

44:19.267 --> 44:21.267
we would have two dead babies

44:22.400 --> 44:25.566
instead of those two beautiful
seven year old children

44:25.567 --> 44:27.100
we all saw speak at trial.

44:28.300 --> 44:29.620
And that's the heart
of this case.

44:33.167 --> 44:37.467
Dana, Nicholas,
I'm Marina Durov. I'm a lawyer.

44:37.700 --> 44:41.732
I'm here to talk to you about
your biological mum and dad.

44:41.733 --> 44:44.432
Do you understand what I mean by
your biological mum and dad?

44:44.433 --> 44:46.332
- No.
- I do.

44:46.333 --> 44:48.399
My real mommy and daddy
aren't my real mommy and daddy,

44:48.400 --> 44:49.799
other ones are.

44:49.800 --> 44:51.466
Nicholas, now do you understand?

44:51.467 --> 44:54.067
Yes, my parents told me about
Staci and James.

44:54.533 --> 44:55.533
That's right.

44:56.733 --> 45:00.633
Staci Horowitz and James Rice
are your biological mom and dad.

45:01.333 --> 45:03.633
Your biological dad
would like to meet you.

45:04.533 --> 45:07.200
- Would you like that, Dana?
- Yes, I would love to meet him.

45:08.133 --> 45:09.532
How about you, Nicholas?

45:09.533 --> 45:12.300
I don't know. Can we talk about
something else?

45:13.600 --> 45:16.300
Yes, we can talk about
something else for a while.

45:16.800 --> 45:20.600
But we have to talk about your
biological daddy again, okay?

45:21.233 --> 45:23.132
Okay,
but can we talk about cars?

45:23.133 --> 45:25.732
I love famous cars.
What kind of cars do you have?

45:25.733 --> 45:27.599
I have all kinds of cars.

45:27.600 --> 45:32.366
I have a Porsche, a Mercedes,
a BMW, a Camaro and a Mustang.

45:32.367 --> 45:34.607
But they are not real cars,
they're just little toy cars.

45:35.300 --> 45:36.333
Okay.

45:43.133 --> 45:47.567
These are two wonderful,
living human beings.

45:49.200 --> 45:51.299
It's a fact that
they would be dead today

45:51.300 --> 45:53.832
if Dr. Wise and the others
hadn't helped Staci.

45:53.833 --> 45:55.633
You're just playing
on our emotions.

45:56.667 --> 45:58.627
This is what I was
talking about before.

45:59.533 --> 46:01.533
Whoever their parents are now,
I'm sure,

46:02.200 --> 46:04.000
couldn't imagine life
without them.

46:04.733 --> 46:08.033
Just watching them
give me chills

46:08.833 --> 46:11.733
thinking they would have been
butchered and not here.

46:36.300 --> 46:39.067
This is my son, Steven.

46:39.833 --> 46:41.633
He's 15. Great kid.

46:42.300 --> 46:43.699
You should see him
play lacrosse.

46:46.233 --> 46:47.166
He's handsome. Bet he's got
a lot of girlfriends, huh?

46:47.167 --> 46:50.199
Oh, yeah.
He's constantly on his phone,

46:50.200 --> 46:52.099
texting, tweeting,
I don't know what.

46:52.100 --> 46:54.199
He doesn't even know
half the kids.

46:54.200 --> 46:56.266
Same with mine.
They're only eight and nine.

46:58.167 --> 46:59.432
You know, I can't remember
the last time

46:59.433 --> 47:01.266
we had a real conversation.

47:01.267 --> 47:04.166
It's like his phone is
surgically attached to his hand.

47:04.167 --> 47:06.000
So, you see where
I'm coming from then?

47:06.533 --> 47:09.067
No. Just the opposite.

47:10.300 --> 47:12.666
The fact that my wife
chose to have my son

47:12.667 --> 47:15.766
doesn't disallow somebody
else from choosing not to.

47:15.767 --> 47:17.499
Steven's a great kid,

47:17.500 --> 47:21.299
but when he was just conceived,
even after a couple of months,

47:21.300 --> 47:23.532
he was still just that
lump of cells.

47:23.533 --> 47:25.099
So, it would have been all right

47:25.100 --> 47:26.733
if he'd been aborted
by your wife?

47:27.733 --> 47:31.299
Abortion is legal. If she'd
wanted to have it, she could.

47:31.300 --> 47:33.166
If the man wanted
the abortion to happen,

47:33.167 --> 47:34.732
he could have wanted that too.

47:34.733 --> 47:37.066
They could do with it
whatever they wanted to.

47:37.067 --> 47:38.187
Now, he's an "it"?

47:40.467 --> 47:43.200
Taking out the humanity
makes it easier, doesn't it?

47:46.367 --> 47:47.367
Not guilty.

47:50.300 --> 47:52.267
These two beautiful children
deserve to live.

47:55.067 --> 47:56.666
And I feel awful.

47:56.667 --> 48:00.200
You feel awful?
Why do you feel awful?

48:01.567 --> 48:03.233
Because I voted
not guilty before.

48:04.700 --> 48:06.332
And that no matter
how it was done

48:06.333 --> 48:08.767
these beautiful children
would not be alive.

48:11.400 --> 48:14.600
I had never thought of it
this way at all, but...

48:17.333 --> 48:19.253
their lives are just more
important than the law.

48:21.567 --> 48:22.567
And you are right.

48:25.500 --> 48:26.533
Not guilty.

48:28.800 --> 48:30.599
You wanted
the expert report charts

48:30.600 --> 48:33.300
on child development
in the womb?

48:34.367 --> 48:36.566
Yes, how did you know?

48:36.567 --> 48:39.266
Oh, either I'm a mind reader

48:39.267 --> 48:43.366
or secretly and illegally
listening to your deliberations.

48:43.367 --> 48:44.367
Or...

48:45.633 --> 48:48.266
Or I quietly picked up the phone
and asked the secretary for them

48:48.267 --> 48:50.432
while we were watching the
twins' testimony.

48:50.433 --> 48:51.433
Or that.

48:52.700 --> 48:54.732
I allowed into evidence

48:54.733 --> 48:57.199
the twins custody battle
deposition testimony

48:57.200 --> 48:58.699
and the deposition testimony
from the real father

48:58.700 --> 49:00.100
for a reason.

49:02.100 --> 49:04.099
And what was that, Your Honor?

49:04.100 --> 49:07.133
I find it irrelevant whether as
the defendants are guilty

49:08.267 --> 49:10.367
for kidnapping Staci Horowitz.

49:11.600 --> 49:13.567
I didn't find it irrelevant.

49:16.067 --> 49:17.832
I had another question
about the law.

49:17.833 --> 49:18.833
Yes?

49:19.600 --> 49:21.267
Let's say we have
the following facts.

49:22.267 --> 49:24.466
Jennifer is pregnant,
she wants to keep the baby,

49:24.467 --> 49:28.299
but Kelly is jealous of her
and tries to kill the baby

49:28.300 --> 49:31.033
by swinging a baseball bat
into her stomach.

49:31.500 --> 49:34.433
Then, Michael,
who's in a wheelchair,

49:35.100 --> 49:37.166
shoots and kills Kelly
to stop her

49:37.167 --> 49:39.327
from killing the baby that's
inside Jennifer's stomach.

49:39.767 --> 49:41.499
Why is Michael in a wheelchair?

49:42.700 --> 49:44.799
I don't know, I just thought
it made it more interesting.

49:44.800 --> 49:46.466
- Right, it did.
- Yup.

49:49.100 --> 49:51.067
So, how old is the fetus?

49:52.467 --> 49:53.732
Let's say two months.

49:53.733 --> 49:57.766
Ah, fetus is two months old, so
Michael shoots and kills Kelly

49:57.767 --> 50:00.232
to prevent her from killing the
fetus. So, the question is,

50:00.233 --> 50:02.232
did he act legally
in defense of another?

50:02.233 --> 50:04.199
Did he have the right to use
lethal force

50:04.200 --> 50:06.733
to save the life of
a two-month-old fetus?

50:11.400 --> 50:14.133
- Your Honor, what's the answer?
- Go through that file first.

50:16.233 --> 50:17.400
Wow, it's cold in here.

50:21.167 --> 50:23.566
I don't know how anyone can sit
through this at trial

50:23.567 --> 50:26.299
and not clearly see a human

50:26.300 --> 50:27.700
growing and changing
by the week?

50:29.733 --> 50:32.267
- Looks like a baby.
- No question.

50:35.767 --> 50:37.667
My turn.
May I have that, please?

50:41.500 --> 50:45.133
